[Fluff] This is probably the least glitchy outcome of devs forgetting to remove a tutor. If Blast Burn's ID was somewhere from 166-255, things would be ranging from very different to very very bad.

6d 6h 17m Back on Route 1, fighting off the rats and birds nibbling at our shoes and occasionally whipping out the TV.

[Info] Since this was never explained here in the updater: The devs forgot to remove the Blast Burn move tutor on the Sevii Isles, and we taught it to Charizard while we were there. Blast Burn obviously is not a generation 1 move, and in fact has an ID higher than Gen 1's one-byte (256) limit, being 307 (or 0x133 in hex). When we shifted over to Gen 1, the higher byte of Blast Burn's ID got lopped off and became Acid (ID 51, or 0x33).

[Info] Charizard's second move is still Acid.
